CAPE TOWN, South Africa, October 26, 2017/APO Group/ --
                                                
                        The Presiding Officers together with the management of Parliament today appeared before the Joint Standing Committee on the Financial Management of Parliament to discuss the institution’s annual report for the financial year 2016/17.





The Committee is satisfied with the nature and spirit of the engagement with the top management of Parliament and the presence and participation of the Presiding Officers.



The Joint Standing Committee on the Financial Management of Parliament was informed by Parliament’s Executive Authority (National Assembly Speaker and National Council of Provinces Chairperson) that they will on Friday receive the report on the investigation relating to allegations against Secretary to Parliament Mr Gengezi Mgidlana.



Mr Mgidlana asked to be placed on special leave in June this year while allegations levelled against him by the National Education, Health and Allied Workers’ Union (Nehawu) were investigated.



“The Committee also welcomes the confirmation from the Presiding Officers that they will receive the report of the investigation into allegations against the Secretary to Parliament, and that they will act on it”, said Committee Co-chairperson Mr Vincent Smith.